In this article, Larry Kudlow, the National Economic Council Director, praises President Trump for his economic achievements and argues that his leadership has led to extraordinary growth in the US economy. Kudlow highlights Trump's commitment to keeping his campaign promises, including tax cuts, regulatory reduction, and challenging international agreements. Kudlow also emphasizes Trump's passion for trade reform, advocating for fair and reciprocal trade. He argues that previous administrations have failed to address these issues, but Trump has taken decisive actions to protect American workers. Kudlow acknowledges that tariffs are not his preferred policy tool but sees them as a necessary response to unfair trading practices.